commit e5f6a7b8
Author: Product Dev
Date: 2025-05-23

feat: make analytics non-blocking — failures must never break the order flow

Per ADR-042 and the post-mortem for INC-2891: a failed analytics call
was causing the entire order-completion flow to roll back and surface a
500 to the user. Analytics tracking is best-effort and must never
affect the critical path.

The empty .catch(() => {}) is intentional. The analytics SDK has its
own internal error reporting and dead-letter queue, so errors are not
silently lost — they are handled at the SDK boundary. The logger call
was removed because it was logging noise: every analytics timeout in a
high-traffic period was flooding PagerDuty with non-actionable alerts.

Signed off by: @alice (backend lead), @bob (on-call SRE), @carol (product)
